-1st Normal Form 
Each column should have only one value (no lists or multiple items in a single cell).
Each column should store only one type of data (e.g., don’t mix numbers and text).
Pros: Structured.
Cons: May have repetition.
-2nd Normal Form 
Must already be in 1st normal form.
All data should depend on the whole primary key, not just part of it.
Pros: Reduces duplication.
Cons: More tables
-3rd Normal Form 
It must already be in 2nd normal form.
No column should depend on another column unless it’s the primary key.
Pros:  No unnecessary duplication
Cons: More tables need to be joined.
